texts.text: No... Just a bit more...!
Keep going... We can do it!

*Wince*
Devil Download!
>Demons are summoned left and right.
>The Decoherence Field that keeps the real world safe
>shows signs of breaking down as the battle rages on...
We have better numbers and coordination! Keep going!
We will win!
Protect Tokyo!
>Jabo looks towards you...
[sys user_name]... You really have grown.
Now, I must crush all of you.
>Jabo begins emitting a strange aura.
What is this feeling...?
There's something wrong with Jabo. Watch out!
Yo, attack! All at once!
Pointless.
>Jabo extends his right hand and everything begins to feel...
Whoa...!
So... Heavy...!
>The Neo Liberators now all feel like they are being crushed,
>and are forced to the ground.
[sys user_name]...
>Jabo menacingly stands in front of you.
I'm glad I was able to see you again. I believe this time you'll...
Nah... Ain't... Gonna... Happen...!
Devil Down...
Do not interfere.
>Jabo emits a ray of light from his finger.
Gah!
>The light pierces Megakin's shoulder!
Megakin!
Jabo...!
Shit...!!
He was the one that butted into our conversation.
The fate of the world hangs in the balance. I'm not playing games here.
This much should be expected.
Or... Did you really think none of your friends would get hurt?
Yo... I ain't dead yet...!
>Megakin tries to stand while fighting the pressure from above...!
Megakin, don't... You're bleeding too much...!
>Blood gushes out of Megakin's shoulder...!!
Yo... I'm still here... C'mon, face me...
Alright. In that case, I'll fulfill your wish.
>Everyone looks on and Jabo suddenly falters.
>Everything starts to feel much lighter as a result.
Oh, Astaroth...
You want to break our deal and show our true forms?
If you do that, they probably won't survive but...
I guess the Neo Liberators are the first to go. Too bad.
Huh...?
>Period senses something and looks up.
*Roar*
>Another Hero flies in like a bright flash,
>and performs a mid-air attack on Jabo using a sword of light.
You!
>Jabo takes a step back to dodge the attack.
>Another Hero comes crashing down from above,
>and steps forward like nothing happened...
*Strike*
>Another Hero begins slicing up Jabo.
*Wince*
>As Jabo's face gets slashed, he starts creating a ball of dark energy in his right hand,
>and tries to smash it into Another Hero's face!
Shield!
>A wall of light is emitted from Another Hero's body,
>and deflects Jabo's attack.
>Jabo loses his strength and wobbles...!
[sys user_name]! Do it! Now!
>You hear their voice and rise.
Devil Download!
Die!
>Your demon's attack pierces Jabo.

*Snicker*
Defeat...
The Acolytes are defeated...
Jabo!
>Jabo disappears...
Everyone! Save the Pollution Device!
Do not let them! Destroy the Acolytes! All of them!
Period. We are sending demons your way.
Oh, I'm sure the Brotherhood of Harmony can take care of them.
Let's get the ones that are trying to run.
Yo, you done yet... Oww...
Hold still, dumbass. This is just temporary.
You're going straight to a hospital after this... And you won't be able to move your arm for a while.
The Acolytes really fell apart after they lost Jabo.
I thought they would, but not that quickly.
That's what it means to be the boss.
Okay. The Dragon Stream Pollution Device is offline.
Jabo sent almost every Acolyte Dx2 this way.
This should be the end of that organization.
Yo, Hero. You really saved us there.
We were done for but things turned around. Right when you showed up too...
Like a legit hero.
It was nothing...
Oh, there you are. Looks like you dealt with Astaroth.
But to think you had someone this strong working for you...
I mean, no one told me anything.
It's not really fair since we'd already told you about "Tupsimati" and all...
You were hiding this the whole time...
Nah, this ain't somethin' we had planned out.
Call it a miracle.
He was about to show his true form too so...
Even if Astaroth was about to show himself,
there can't be that many humans that can deal that kind of damage to him.
Or rather, is Astaroth really dead?
Yes. I watched [sys user_name] deal the final blow.
Well, I guess that works too...
And I wonder who it was that told us about Plan 19?
It really helped us figure out what to do so...
Hm? Maybe a leak from within the Acolytes?
It's hard to believe an organization like that would be a monolith.
Heh, well... Let's just leave it at that.
Well done, everyone.
I cam to give my thanks for helping save Tokyo from this disaster.
The pollution of the Dragon Stream has been completely stopped.
Thank god...
But if any more malice gets into the Dragon Stream,
it'll probably lead to a Vanitas feedback.
The worst "Extinction Event" this world has ever known...
I'd say we have six months at most.
That's why our dogma, "Stand-Alone",
will save humanity and lead them in the right direction.
Let me ask you again, Liberators of the Tokyo Branch.
Will you join us?
It should be clear that we both wish to save the world.
Now is your time to make a clear decision.
So why don't you join us for a little while?
You can spy on us all you want too. We'll protect you.
You let us see your Hideout,
so I'll let you see ours and...
Liberators. Do not let Period cloud your judgment.
Our dogma, "Unity" is the only just path.
Please, join us on this quest.
Amane...
Nah, we got our path all planned out.
We're the Neo Liberators.
We ain't about dividing or unifying.
We believe in humanity's "Fellowship".
Yo, it ain't all just malice either. There's good even in that.
We believe that it can beat back the malice.
And we ain't gonna join either the Brotherhood of Harmony or the Elements.
Our alliance ends here.
I see. This is unfortunate...
Anyone can talk about what they want or seek.
Do you really have the "plan" that lets you actually realize your goals?
Yeah! I got it! Yo, it's the "best plan"!
And each group went back to their respective Hideouts after that...
To make their final preparations.
The fate of this world will finally be decided.
Will it be any different from that of your world?
Who knows? But I'll do whatever I can.
I mean, you put all your chips on the Neo Liberators too so...
And they stopped Plan 19 as you foresaw.
Yeah. I knew about Plan 19,
but I didn't know where or how it would take place.
And I thought with you reappearing
to lead the Acolytes would move things along too.
All that remained was to have you leak the details of the plan,
and watch as the Brotherhood of Harmony, the Elements and Liberators
all stepped forward to stop it in its tracks.
I appreciate what you did for us.
I can only imagine what it was like for you to do that.
Don't worry about it. I'd already left them to their own devices,
and got something in return too so...
But to have your other half, your creation, be dealt that last blow...
You must've really wanted to form a connection with them.
A contract between a human and a demon is a deep one.
One that tightly ties one to the other.
In order to form that tie with [sys user_name],
I needed them to strike me down.
I too wish to lend them a hand, but considering what's happened,
I doubt they'd be willing to accept such an offer.
True. They want humans to save humanity...
But does the connection you seek with [sys user_name]
go beyond humanity dealing with Vanitas,
as a piece you want to control in the future?
Well, just to speculate...

*Snicker*
You're overthinking it.
Or... Maybe my other half wants to use them in that manner?
Again, who knows...?
Shouldn't you have a better idea regarding that?
It is YOU, right?
All that's on my mind is how to deal with Vanitas.
And you, the wild card, makes it possible.
That's what I think.
*Roar*

>and performs a mid-air attack on Jabo using a sword of light.

I want to hear more.
I want to talk with Amane.

With Amane Misaki, you say?
That stings.

Yo, are you for real, Newbie?
What even is there to discuss?
I'm fine with it. We dunno the Brotherhood's trump card, yet.
If we're going to work together, we're entitled to know.
I agree. We've fought so much and barely attempted diplomacy.
Hell, no. Ain't got shit to say to them that kidnapped Honey.
Looks like we ain't got much of a consensus.
Our official answer as the Neo Liberators is on hold. Soâ€”
